name: PARNASO #3 - Maria Comprida
description:
After a break to regain some energy lost in the hiking and to rehydrate, the mind started to work better. One last and closer look at Maria Comprida in all "her" beauty before resuming the trail. In free translation the name of this mountain means something like "Tall Mary". "Her" walls exceed a thousand meters in height and "she" is probably the most remarkable geological monument in Petrópolis.

About the series: Pictures taken in and around the Serra dos Órgãos National Park ('Parque Nacional da Serra dos Órgãos' in portuguese or its abbreviation 'PARNASO'), located in the state of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, and covers a huge area across four municipalities.

Equipment: Sony Alpha A6500 + Sony E 18-135mm F/3.5-5.6 OSS
Location: Petrópolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
